{
  "stem": "3771.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I-- this, the final chapter of the evacuation, or we call it the Death March from Auschwitz, was, like someone said, that was nearly the straw what broke the camel's back.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You couldn't take it anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But somehow, somewhere, they were in me that my parents and that good friend in that-- in Auschwitz-- the one which I had, the-- the professor.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He was a professor in university in-- in Pressburg-- had instilled in me physically impossible.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When doctors came out after and said to me, 'How did you survive?' I had no answer, actually, as to how I survived.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maybe the last drop milk for my dear mother which kept me going, and the kind words.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But one thing I had it in my mind that [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I will have to tell the world at least what transpired, what horrendous thing happened to humanity, what happened to our people.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then I can die.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Where did you go on this Death March?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We actually went through-- from Poland, because they all took us into the Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were many cities and many thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I actually don't remember many names for many of them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because they were hoping that the-- that the Allies will not get into Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they didn't want that we should be left as living witnesses to tell to the world [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] what transpired.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The liberation-- actually when I was liberated, I [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was in a trance.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When finally the Germans left us and they said, you're free-- [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] this is another horrifying chapter, which I would like to dwell on it a little bit and tell it to the world what actually happened after the liberation.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was liberated at Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
